# 1️⃣ STL Basics (Standard Template Library)

---

# First Understand Why STL Exists

Imagine you need:

* Dynamic arrays
* Stacks
* Queues
* Sorting

You could build everything from scratch.

But that's like building your own bicycle every time you want to travel.

❌ Waste of time

So C++ provides ready-made, optimized tools.

That's STL.

---

# Mental Model

```text
STL = Toolbox for Programmers
```

Just like an electrician carries tools,
a programmer carries STL containers.

---

# A. Vector

---

## Problem with Arrays

```cpp
int arr[5];
```

Size is fixed.

What if you need 6 elements?

❌ Problem.

---

## Solution → Vector

```cpp
vector<int> v;
```

Vector can grow automatically.

---

## Example

```cpp
vector<int> v;

v.push_back(10);
v.push_back(20);
v.push_back(30);
```

---

### Memory Visualization

Initially:

```text
10
```

Then:

```text
10 20
```

Then:

```text
10 20 30
```

Vector expands automatically.

---

## Access Elements

```cpp
cout << v[0];
```

Output:

```text
10
```

---

## Useful Operations

```cpp
v.push_back(100);
v.pop_back();

v.size();
```

---

## Mental Model

```text
Vector = Smart Array
```

Remember this forever.

---

# B. Pair

---

## Simple Idea

Store two values together.

---

### Real-World Example

Student Record:

```text
Roll Number + Name
```

Two related values.

---

### Example

```cpp
pair<int,string> p;

p.first = 101;
p.second = "Akshay";
```

---

### Access

```cpp
cout << p.first;
cout << p.second;
```

---

## Mental Model

```text
Pair = Two-item box
```

---

# C. Stack

---

## Simple Idea

Follows:

# LIFO

```text
Last In First Out
```

---

## Real-World Example

Stack of plates:

```text
Plate3
Plate2
Plate1
```

Last plate placed comes out first.

---

### Example

```cpp
stack<int> st;

st.push(10);
st.push(20);
st.push(30);
```

---

### Visualization

```text
30 ← top
20
10
```

---

### Remove

```cpp
st.pop();
```

Now:

```text
20 ← top
10
```

---

### Access Top

```cpp
st.top();
```

---

## Mental Model

```text
Stack = Plate Stack
```

---

# D. Queue

---

## Simple Idea

Follows:

# FIFO

```text
First In First Out
```

---

## Real-World Example

Movie ticket line.

Person entering first gets served first.

---

### Example

```cpp
queue<int> q;

q.push(10);
q.push(20);
q.push(30);
```

---

### Visualization

```text
Front → 10 20 30 ← Rear
```

---

### Remove

```cpp
q.pop();
```

Removes:

```text
10
```

---

### Access Front

```cpp
q.front();
```

---

## Mental Model

```text
Queue = Waiting Line
```

---

