# 2️⃣ Time Complexity (MOST IMPORTANT)

---

# Why Time Complexity Exists

Imagine two programs:

Program A:

```text
1 second
```

Program B:

```text
100 seconds
```

Both give same answer.

Which is better?

Obviously:

```text
Program A
```

So we measure efficiency.

---

# What is Time Complexity?

It tells:

```text
How runtime grows as input grows.
```

---

# Mental Model

Don't think:

```text
Exact seconds
```

Think:

```text
Growth rate
```

---

# Example 1

```cpp
for(int i=0; i<n; i++)
{
    cout << i;
}
```

Runs n times.

Time Complexity:

```text
O(n)
```

Read as:

```text
Order of n
```

---

# Example 2

```cpp
for(int i=0; i<n; i++)
{
    for(int j=0; j<n; j++)
    {
        cout << i;
    }
}
```

Runs:

```text
n × n
```

Complexity:

```text
O(n²)
```

---

# Visualization

If:

```text
n = 10
```

Then:

```text
100 operations
```

If:

```text
n = 100
```

Then:

```text
10000 operations
```

Growth becomes huge.

---

# Most Important Complexities

| Complexity | Meaning   |
| ---------- | --------- |
| O(1)       | Constant  |
| O(log n)   | Very fast |
| O(n)       | Linear    |
| O(n log n) | Efficient |
| O(n²)      | Slow      |
| O(2ⁿ)      | Very slow |

---

# Real-World Analogy

Finding a student in class.

### O(1)

Teacher points directly.

```text
Instant
```

---

### O(n)

Check students one by one.

---

### O(log n)

Class sorted by roll number.

Keep dividing search area.

Very fast.

---

# Why Interviewers Care

Companies don't want code that works only for:

```text
n = 10
```

They want code that works for:

```text
n = 10,00,000
```

Efficiently.

---

# Shortcut for Placements 🔥

### Single Loop

```cpp
for(...)
```

👉 O(n)

---

### Nested Loop

```cpp
for(...)
{
    for(...)
}
```

👉 O(n²)

---

### Divide by 2 Every Time

```cpp
while(n)
{
    n /= 2;
}
```

👉 O(log n)

---

# How to Remember Forever

Think:

```text
Time Complexity = Growth of work
```

NOT

```text
Actual seconds
```

